WEBVTT

00:07.008 --> 00:11.798
(theme music plays )

00:11.971 --> 00:15.714
(thunder rumbling, rain pouring)

00:18.644 --> 00:21.932
Batiatus:
We have seen misfortune,

00:22.106 --> 00:24.848
felt the sting of defeat,

00:25.026 --> 00:28.189
the humility of vacant purse
and empty stomach.

00:28.362 --> 00:30.978
Some believed
the House of Batiatus

00:31.157 --> 00:33.364
would never reclaim
its former glory,

00:33.534 --> 00:35.525
that we would fade
from memory,

00:35.703 --> 00:38.194
forsaken by history.

00:38.372 --> 00:40.033
But we have
proved them wrong!

00:40.208 --> 00:41.948
Men: Yeah!

00:42.126 --> 00:43.866
We have proved
the name Batiatus

00:44.045 --> 00:46.502
will live long after we have gone
to dust and bone.

00:46.672 --> 00:48.003
Men: Yeah!

00:48.174 --> 00:51.587
So stand proud before
the bringer of rain,

00:51.761 --> 00:55.003
the slayer
of the shadow of death,

00:55.181 --> 00:57.843
the new champion of Capua:

00:58.017 --> 00:59.757
Spartacus!

00:59.936 --> 01:03.053
(all cheering )

01:13.324 --> 01:15.986
( men chanting )
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:16.160 --> 01:17.991
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:18.162 --> 01:20.744
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:20.915 --> 01:22.906
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:23.084 --> 01:25.700
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:25.878 --> 01:27.493
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:27.672 --> 01:30.038
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:30.216 --> 01:32.457
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:32.635 --> 01:35.752
Spartacus! Spartacus!

01:36.764 --> 01:39.551
(groaning)

01:42.270 --> 01:43.885
( crowd gasps )

01:49.944 --> 01:53.357
(thunder booming)

01:54.740 --> 01:57.482
(screaming )

01:57.660 --> 01:59.901
(all cheering )

02:00.079 --> 02:03.742
A titan-- his victory
eclipsing all others,

02:03.916 --> 02:06.999
quenching our thirst,

02:10.256 --> 02:12.668
Behold the man
as he becomes legend.

02:12.842 --> 02:14.958
Men: Yeah!

02:20.599 --> 02:21.975
This is only the beginning.

02:22.143 --> 02:25.635
I will build an empire of blood
and glory upon your name.

02:25.813 --> 02:28.930
He did not stand
against Theokoles on his own.

02:29.108 --> 02:30.644
Crixus is not forgotten.

02:30.818 --> 02:33.935
He will always have position...
if he survives.

02:34.113 --> 02:36.274
But Spartacus is the name
on the crowd's tongue

02:36.449 --> 02:39.316
and I would see it spoken
with ever-increasing amazement.

02:39.493 --> 02:42.326
l defeated a man
who could not be defeated.

02:42.496 --> 02:44.236
What more could
they expect of me?

02:44.415 --> 02:47.498
( laughs)
Everything!

02:47.668 --> 02:49.249
Their appetite is a great beast;

02:49.420 --> 02:51.661
it must constantly be fed
with new delights.

02:51.839 --> 02:53.875
We'll start by changing
your fighting style--

02:54.050 --> 02:56.837
two swords as Theokoles fought with.

02:57.011 --> 03:00.754
We'll see the crowd's pleasure double
with their new hero twice as deadly

03:00.931 --> 03:03.593
and new armor worthy of a legend.

03:05.603 --> 03:07.559
Women will moisten at the very sight.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.647
Ah, but I forget.

03:12.818 --> 03:15.195
He has no hard purpose
forjust any wet thigh, does he?

03:15.363 --> 03:18.480
He and his purpose
are not my concern.

03:18.657 --> 03:20.909
Batiatus:
Fortunately the gods feel otherwise.

03:21.077 --> 03:24.160
They shower him with more
than rain and accolades.

03:24.330 --> 03:26.912
They bless him with news
to lift the heart

03:27.083 --> 03:29.369
higher than the clouds.

03:29.543 --> 03:30.703
Sura?

03:30.878 --> 03:33.915
Found in the dark corners of Syria.

03:34.090 --> 03:35.330
Where-- where is she?
Is she well?

03:35.508 --> 03:36.998
Peace.

03:37.176 --> 03:39.337
All will be revealed
when a mouth closes.

03:39.512 --> 03:41.252
The Syrian Glaber spoke of
sold her to a merchant--

03:41.430 --> 03:42.465
the sea his mistress.

03:42.640 --> 03:44.676
They have recently docked
on the shores of Neapolis.

03:44.850 --> 03:47.057
- On Roman soil?
- Your wife among the slaves.

03:47.228 --> 03:49.719
Two days' ride from where you stand,
barring incident.

03:49.897 --> 03:52.309
- When do we leave?
- Is it wise to allow such a thing?

03:52.483 --> 03:54.724
My man already spurns his horse.
Rest at ease.

03:54.902 --> 03:56.984
She moves ever closer
even as we speak.

04:03.202 --> 04:05.614
You are an honorable man

04:05.788 --> 04:07.824
and will forever bear my gratitude.

04:07.998 --> 04:10.489
As you bear mine.

04:10.668 --> 04:14.035
Being reunited with your wife
is but the first of many rewards.

04:15.548 --> 04:17.379
Dominus.

04:24.306 --> 04:26.137
Secrets.

04:26.308 --> 04:28.970
Secrets upon secrets.

04:29.145 --> 04:31.978
News of her discovery
only just reached me.

04:32.148 --> 04:34.184
And what of good Ovidius
and his family?

04:35.443 --> 04:39.402
Why did you keep plans
towards their slaughter from me?

04:39.572 --> 04:41.483
And all to clear a few debts?

04:41.657 --> 04:44.444
It had nothing to do with debt,
except one of blood.

04:44.618 --> 04:47.200
His was the hand behind
attempt on my life in the pits.

04:47.371 --> 04:51.410
- Ovidius?
- Moved to purpose by Solonius.

04:54.587 --> 04:56.953
I keep from you not out of secrecy,
but from love.

04:57.131 --> 05:00.339
I would not have you stained
by such things.

05:00.509 --> 05:02.670
We are the toast of the fucking city!

05:02.845 --> 05:05.461
Let us pause and enjoy it.

05:22.448 --> 05:23.563
Doctore:
Yours alone.

05:23.741 --> 05:25.823
Not to be shared?

05:25.993 --> 05:27.779
Your achievement
in earning it profound.

05:27.953 --> 05:30.239
Made possible by your instruction.

05:30.414 --> 05:33.121
My actions only set you
to the task.

05:33.292 --> 05:35.374
By depriving Theokoles of his life,

05:35.544 --> 05:39.913
you put end to a battle
left unfinished by my sword,

05:40.090 --> 05:41.591
an end to my shame.

05:44.178 --> 05:48.717
| live to see my wife again
because of you...

05:48.891 --> 05:51.132
a debt not soon forgotten.

05:51.310 --> 05:54.222
There is no balance between us,

05:54.396 --> 05:56.887
only the promise of future glory.

06:01.195 --> 06:04.028
Are candles permitted?

06:04.198 --> 06:06.860
Sura was always fond of them.

06:07.034 --> 06:09.650
You misunderstand.

06:09.828 --> 06:11.989
This cell is for you alone.

06:12.164 --> 06:14.029
Wives are not permitted
to live among us.

06:14.208 --> 06:15.948
Then where will she stay?

06:16.126 --> 06:18.538
In the villa,
kept safe and well

06:18.712 --> 06:21.124
in return for good service
to the domina.

06:21.298 --> 06:24.756
- As a slave.
- As are we all.

06:26.136 --> 06:29.799
But you rise quickly,
unlike any other I've ever witnessed.

06:29.974 --> 06:32.932
Continue your ascent
and you will gain freedom

06:33.102 --> 06:35.058
for both of you.

06:39.149 --> 06:41.140
(thunder rumbling)

06:45.573 --> 06:47.313
Barca: Ashur.

06:49.410 --> 06:50.946
Barca!

06:51.120 --> 06:53.076
l was this very moment
coming to have word.

06:53.247 --> 06:55.738
Keep them.
lwould have coin instead.

06:55.916 --> 06:58.999
This is no small marvel--
the fall of Theokoles.

06:59.169 --> 07:01.455
Your wager in the favor
of the unexpected outcome,

07:01.630 --> 07:03.871
the size of the odds...

07:04.049 --> 07:06.381
It's not a simple matter
to cover a win of such margin, huh?

07:06.552 --> 07:08.258
(shouts, grunts)

07:08.429 --> 07:10.795
I give no shit for margins.

07:10.973 --> 07:13.806
Beg, steal or kill
to cover what is owed

07:13.976 --> 07:15.341
or you will have
two worthless legs

07:15.519 --> 07:17.680
and nothing in between
to prop yourself up.

07:17.855 --> 07:20.392
(gasping )

07:26.488 --> 07:28.479
( cooing )

07:30.951 --> 07:32.942
(tsking )

07:39.460 --> 07:41.200
I've had exchange with the cripple.

07:41.378 --> 07:42.754
He pays what is owed?

07:42.921 --> 07:46.084
Soon the coin will be in hand,
enough to buy our freedom.

07:52.014 --> 07:54.050
"Freedom..."

07:54.224 --> 07:56.215
the word is foreign to the tongue.

07:56.393 --> 07:58.224
It will learn to savor the taste.

07:58.395 --> 08:00.056
What of the birds?

08:00.230 --> 08:02.562
They'll fly this place, as we do.

08:02.733 --> 08:04.644
I'll see what clothes we have
packed and ready.

08:05.944 --> 08:08.856
Which direction shall we travel
and how far?

08:09.031 --> 08:12.068
As far as desire wills our feet.

08:13.744 --> 08:15.985
This cloak...

08:16.163 --> 08:18.495
it was the one you wore
when you left,

08:18.666 --> 08:19.906
when good Ovidius was murdered.

08:20.084 --> 08:21.290
There was nothing good about him.

08:21.460 --> 08:23.200
Then it was you who killed him?

08:23.379 --> 08:25.586
All his slaves, his family?

08:25.756 --> 08:27.667
My hands did what
they were commanded.

08:27.841 --> 08:30.378
What of the young boy--
Ovidius's son?

08:30.552 --> 08:31.758
Did they take his life too?

08:31.929 --> 08:34.841
Such were my orders,

08:35.015 --> 08:37.802
but you know of my affection
for delicate things.

08:39.478 --> 08:41.844
The boy was spared

08:42.022 --> 08:43.637
and set to wander far from the deed.

08:43.816 --> 08:46.182
By the time he is discovered,
we will be free.

08:47.194 --> 08:48.695
And your hands?

08:48.862 --> 08:53.026
Clean forevermore
and yours to command.

09:28.277 --> 09:30.984
Spartacus's victory ignites
the imagination of the city!

09:31.155 --> 09:33.396
Orders for my men flood in
from every family

09:33.574 --> 09:35.064
with half a name and a little coin.

09:35.242 --> 09:37.904
Prosperity beyond measure
is within our reach.

09:38.078 --> 09:40.319
As are those who would
have you dead.

09:41.457 --> 09:43.539
I will see Solonius pay
for the grievance.

09:43.709 --> 09:46.667
But these things are not be hurried.

09:46.837 --> 09:49.419
I would savor every drop
of sweat from his brow

09:49.590 --> 09:52.423
as my noose tightens
upon his neck.

09:52.593 --> 09:55.255
lwould prefer it tighten quickly.

09:55.429 --> 09:57.294
Uh, everything to its season.

09:57.473 --> 09:59.429
Turning towards
more pressing matters...

09:59.600 --> 10:02.637
Reuniting the Thracian with his wife?

10:02.811 --> 10:05.393
Not the matter I was referring to.

10:05.564 --> 10:10.775
Have the girl's ass a bit
and I'll watch.

10:10.944 --> 10:13.401
And lwould give pleasure
to your eyes.

10:19.620 --> 10:22.703
(grunting)

10:27.503 --> 10:29.915
The Thracian woman concerns me.

10:31.882 --> 10:33.838
The promise of finding her
was the only thing

10:34.009 --> 10:36.000
that kept him in check.

10:36.178 --> 10:39.090
What if her presence reverts him
to his Thracian ways

10:39.264 --> 10:42.006
and thoughts of defiance?

10:42.184 --> 10:43.924
It will not.

10:44.102 --> 10:46.593
How can you be so sure?

10:46.772 --> 10:49.639
Did you see the tears of gratitude
in his eyes?

10:50.901 --> 10:53.768
Gratitude falls short of loyalty.

10:55.405 --> 10:57.487
He's not the man Crixus is.

10:57.658 --> 10:59.194
And Crixus is not the man he was,

10:59.368 --> 11:03.111
and may never be again.

11:04.414 --> 11:08.623
Spartacus will be reunited
with his wife.

11:08.794 --> 11:12.412
And in the act,
lwill bind him to us

11:12.589 --> 11:14.500
and this ludus

11:14.675 --> 11:18.133
until God comes
to claim us all.

11:23.308 --> 11:25.685
(thunder rumbling)

11:44.371 --> 11:46.487
Varro:
How will you save us...

11:47.833 --> 11:49.448
from the rain?

11:49.626 --> 11:51.127
Your victory splits the skies.

11:51.295 --> 11:53.411
How will you close them
before we all drown?

11:53.589 --> 11:55.375
You believe
the rest of the fools, then?

11:55.549 --> 11:57.164
That I am blessed by the gods?

11:57.342 --> 11:59.674
Miracles do take habit
of shooting out of your ass.

11:59.845 --> 12:02.712
( chuckles )

12:02.890 --> 12:06.508
I've heard whispers of yet
more divine providence.

12:06.685 --> 12:09.848
Sura-- is it true?

12:10.022 --> 12:12.559
She speeds to my arms
from Neapolis.

12:12.733 --> 12:15.725
And still you doubt
the gods favor you.

12:15.903 --> 12:17.768
If what Sura has been
forced to endure

12:17.946 --> 12:20.688
is parcel of their favor, I would rather
they turn their back on me.

12:20.866 --> 12:22.652
- If they exist at all.
- She comes.

12:22.826 --> 12:24.566
That is all that matters now.

12:24.745 --> 12:26.736
Yeah.

12:27.998 --> 12:30.614
You once lived free in these lands.

12:30.792 --> 12:33.329
From which way does she travel?

12:33.503 --> 12:35.755
The port in Neapolis
lies in that direction.

12:35.923 --> 12:37.709
(thunder rumbling)

12:37.883 --> 12:39.623
Are there roads to the mountains
that lead east?

12:39.801 --> 12:41.302
Several.

12:41.470 --> 12:43.586
Which ones are
the most sparsely traveled?

12:43.764 --> 12:46.927
An odd question,
removed from the subject.

12:47.100 --> 12:49.682
Not so far astray.

12:51.521 --> 12:54.684
Yes, some are sparsely travelled,
but not to the point

12:54.858 --> 12:56.598
of the new champion
of fucking Capua

12:56.777 --> 12:59.314
going unnoticed if overcome
by questionable thoughts.

12:59.488 --> 13:03.401
How long do you think before Batiatus
would allow me to buy our freedom?

13:03.575 --> 13:06.032
How many years will she be
condemned to bow and scrape?

13:06.203 --> 13:07.443
Death the alternative?

13:07.621 --> 13:09.953
You move to escape beyond these walls,
and that is surely what you'll find.

13:10.123 --> 13:11.624
Has no one ever attempted
such a thing?

13:11.792 --> 13:13.532
And lived? No.

13:13.710 --> 13:15.871
It is a thing born of the impossible.

13:16.046 --> 13:18.708
The same was said
of defeating Theokoles.

13:18.882 --> 13:20.622
You have a plan, then?

13:20.801 --> 13:23.338
One begins to take shape.

13:23.512 --> 13:25.093
Ahh!

13:27.391 --> 13:29.677
( screams )

13:30.769 --> 13:33.101
( all shouting )

13:36.858 --> 13:39.691
( roaring )

13:53.542 --> 13:56.204
( roaring )

13:59.506 --> 14:01.462
Ooh!

14:08.223 --> 14:10.305
That's your plan?

14:10.475 --> 14:12.887
- I fear it malformed.
- In what way?

14:13.061 --> 14:14.642
Weapons, to begin.

14:14.813 --> 14:18.351
- In large supply at a ludus.
- Ah, but kept by lock and key.

14:18.525 --> 14:20.311
Or do you believe the gods
will drop one from the sky

14:20.485 --> 14:22.191
along with the rain?

14:22.362 --> 14:24.478
I believe in opportunity.

14:24.656 --> 14:26.692
And the power of reason
to seize upon it.

14:26.867 --> 14:28.073
Fair enough.

14:28.243 --> 14:30.825
Say you somehow reason up a weapon. What
of a horse?

14:30.996 --> 14:33.157
You'll never reach
the mountains without one.

14:33.331 --> 14:35.583
Dominus provides one.

14:35.751 --> 14:37.833
Sura arrives by cart.

14:38.003 --> 14:40.745
(neighing)

14:50.348 --> 14:51.724
Well, it won't matter.

14:51.892 --> 14:55.009
Weapons, horses--
they're the least of your concerns.

14:55.187 --> 14:56.677
And the greatest?

14:56.855 --> 14:59.187
The one man that could stop you.

15:01.526 --> 15:05.360
Ahh!

15:11.787 --> 15:13.743
(Sura cries out)

15:13.914 --> 15:16.701
Uh!

15:35.227 --> 15:36.433
Yah!

15:41.942 --> 15:42.977
I had not considered him.

15:43.151 --> 15:44.891
You have not considered many things.

15:45.070 --> 15:47.061
Take pause, I beg of you.

15:47.239 --> 15:51.198
No. We will have our freedom.

15:51.368 --> 15:54.485
I will take her in my arms
and hear her speak my name--

15:54.663 --> 15:56.324
my name,

15:56.498 --> 15:58.705
not the one the Romans
branded me with.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.957
- I cannot help you in this.
- I would not ask it.

16:01.128 --> 16:03.039
- If it weren't for my own family...
- Give it no thought.

16:03.213 --> 16:05.625
Is there nothing I can say
to turn you from this path?

16:05.799 --> 16:07.505
Nothing.

16:09.219 --> 16:11.801
Then may the gods
you don't believe in favor you.

16:21.690 --> 16:23.851
(thunderclaps )

16:54.181 --> 16:55.967
Batiatus:
A fine figure, is he not?

16:56.141 --> 16:57.847
A god among men.

16:58.018 --> 17:00.760
I've never beheld
such magnificent armor.

17:03.857 --> 17:06.018
If you grant permission,

17:06.193 --> 17:08.149
I would wear it
upon my wife's return.

17:08.320 --> 17:09.856
A move to impress?

17:11.907 --> 17:14.865
- She will marvel at the sight.
- ( thunderclap )

17:26.087 --> 17:29.921
( roaring )

17:36.264 --> 17:39.427
( roaring )

17:41.686 --> 17:44.223
A man must always appear
his best in the eyes of love.

17:44.397 --> 17:45.432
You may wear it.

17:45.607 --> 17:47.598
I will even stand by your side
while you welcome her

17:47.776 --> 17:49.232
with your open arms.

17:49.402 --> 17:50.687
The swords, however...

17:50.862 --> 17:52.568
What need would I have of them?

17:56.826 --> 17:58.782
Calavius:
Can it be?

17:58.954 --> 18:00.865
The legend himself among us?

18:01.039 --> 18:03.701
Magistrate Calavius.
Good fortune to see you.

18:03.875 --> 18:05.581
No, the good fortune is mine.

18:05.752 --> 18:08.289
My son Numerius cannot cease
his talk of Spartacus

18:08.463 --> 18:10.169
and his victory over Theokoles.

18:11.174 --> 18:12.459
He demanded
a trip to market

18:12.634 --> 18:16.172
to obtain something of Thrace
in your man's honor.

18:16.346 --> 18:17.836
Show him.

18:19.724 --> 18:21.715
The merchant said
it was a warrior's weapon.

18:27.107 --> 18:29.644
As well it is.

18:30.735 --> 18:33.522
See these marks?

18:33.697 --> 18:37.315
Thracians notch their hilts--
one for every kill.

18:38.952 --> 18:41.568
Numerius: How many made to yours
after slaying Theokoles?

18:41.746 --> 18:44.203
He must have been
worth 10 at least.

18:44.374 --> 18:45.363
Spartacus: Hmm.

18:45.542 --> 18:47.954
If I could wield a sword
half as well you...

18:50.463 --> 18:53.955
Join us at my master's ludus

18:54.134 --> 18:57.718
and I will teach you the blow
that brought death to the shadow.

18:57.887 --> 19:00.754
Batiatus:
A splendid notion.

19:00.932 --> 19:03.048
Numerius: Father?

19:03.226 --> 19:05.433
Perhaps a visit later
this afternoon.

19:05.603 --> 19:07.594
Batiatus: Why make the boy
suffer with anticipation?

19:07.772 --> 19:08.978
Join us presently.

19:09.149 --> 19:11.640
Joy must be delayed
in favor of sorrow.

19:11.818 --> 19:14.605
I attend to matters relating
to my cousin's murder.

19:15.739 --> 19:17.229
Batiatus:
Good Ovidius.

19:17.407 --> 19:19.398
The heart constricts at the thought.

19:19.576 --> 19:22.113
But swells with promise of vengeance.

19:23.913 --> 19:25.039
Numerius, come.

19:25.206 --> 19:28.118
Your generous hospitality
will be appreciated shortly.

19:29.794 --> 19:31.785
(grunts)

19:35.592 --> 19:38.550
An invitation to school
the magistrate's son?

19:38.720 --> 19:42.133
Apologies if I offered out of turn.

19:42.307 --> 19:44.093
Fuck apologies.

19:44.267 --> 19:46.474
Shrewd maneuvering,
if ever I saw it!

19:46.644 --> 19:48.145
I'll make a Roman of you yet!

19:48.313 --> 19:50.554
(laughing)

19:58.823 --> 20:01.405
Should his eyes not be open?

20:01.576 --> 20:03.567
Calm is needed to heal the wound.

20:03.745 --> 20:05.701
I keep him at rest with herb.

20:05.872 --> 20:08.659
- He will recover?
- I've done what I can.

20:08.833 --> 20:10.949
lt rests in the hands of the gods.

20:11.127 --> 20:13.243
No.

20:13.421 --> 20:16.458
