43:57.552 --> 44:00.510
Doctore's usually up before the sun,
whip in hand.

44:01.515 --> 44:03.130
Will he ever rise again?

44:03.308 --> 44:05.845
He will, but not for many hours.

44:06.019 --> 44:08.977
Oh, your chances improve then.

44:09.147 --> 44:13.060
- To the point of certainty.
- Nothing is ever so.

44:13.235 --> 44:16.022
Look, even if you ride beyond the gates,
the guards will pursue.

44:16.196 --> 44:18.061
They will be commanded
against such action.

44:19.950 --> 44:21.531
You actually expect them
to obey you?

44:21.701 --> 44:22.781
No.

44:22.953 --> 44:25.615
I expect them to obey their master.

44:29.584 --> 44:33.827
Drop your fucking swords!
Do it!

44:34.005 --> 44:38.044
I will release him when we are
in the cover of the mountains.

44:38.218 --> 44:39.924
Batiatus: Spartacus!

44:40.095 --> 44:42.427
Your wife's cart
appears on the road.

44:42.597 --> 44:45.009
I'll be with you presently.

44:45.183 --> 44:48.050
I urge you to reconsider
one last time.

44:48.228 --> 44:50.514
Sura will be free

44:50.689 --> 44:54.352
in this life, or the one after,

44:54.526 --> 44:56.642
with her husband by her side.

45:00.824 --> 45:04.362
Then may the gods see you both
upon the plains of Thrace.

45:13.837 --> 45:15.828
(thunderclaps )

45:26.850 --> 45:28.806
Lucretia:
The pool is clear,

45:28.977 --> 45:30.968
as if it never happened.

45:31.146 --> 45:33.307
A regrettable misunderstanding.

45:36.693 --> 45:38.979
He wished for his freedom.

45:39.154 --> 45:41.691
A betrayal in itself.

45:44.242 --> 45:45.698
Come, to happier thoughts.

45:45.869 --> 45:47.825
The Thracian's wife approaches.

45:47.996 --> 45:50.237
How is that a cause for cheer?

45:50.415 --> 45:51.996
Her arrival will only remind him

45:52.167 --> 45:53.657
of his old life
and the ways of an animal.

45:53.835 --> 45:55.416
Why can't you see that?

45:55.587 --> 45:57.794
Our hopes and fortunes
are tied to Spartacus.

45:57.964 --> 45:59.829
I made a promise
to reunite him with his wife.

46:00.008 --> 46:03.091
In honor of the man,
I will keep my word.

46:46.471 --> 46:48.086
( horse neighs)

47:00.443 --> 47:03.606
Man:
Opening the gates!

47:04.739 --> 47:08.072
A carriage approaches...

47:31.641 --> 47:34.178
Whoa.

47:34.352 --> 47:36.843
Whoa.

48:08.553 --> 48:10.885
( yawns )

48:25.945 --> 48:28.687
( neighs )

49:02.690 --> 49:04.601
(grunts)

49:12.033 --> 49:15.070
( groans )

49:15.245 --> 49:18.282
Driver: They came
out of nowhere, on the road.

49:18.456 --> 49:22.495
( echoing ) They attacked--
they attacked on the road.

51:08.066 --> 51:10.057
I'm here.

51:43.268 --> 51:46.510
My word is kept.

51:46.688 --> 51:48.895
They're reunited.
